16:05.471 --> 16:07.440
DAMN.

16:26.459 --> 16:28.795
HEY, CANDACE,
YOU HAVE TO CALL ME.

16:28.795 --> 16:30.564
CALL ME, PLEASE.

16:37.070 --> 16:38.505
EXCUSE ME.

16:46.713 --> 16:47.881
HELLO?

16:47.881 --> 16:50.050
<i>JEFFERY?</i>

16:50.050 --> 16:51.217
YEAH?

16:51.217 --> 16:52.953
I CAN'T GET TO THE BACKYARD.

16:55.288 --> 16:56.590
UH, WHY?

16:56.590 --> 16:58.925
'CAUSE THERE'S OFFICERS
EVERYWHERE.

16:58.925 --> 17:02.002
DAMN. UH.

17:02.002 --> 17:04.505
<i>WHAT'S IN THE BACKYARD?</i>

17:04.505 --> 17:07.808
UM, I ‐‐ I ‐‐ IT'S ‐‐ IT'S ‐‐

17:07.808 --> 17:09.175
TELL ME.

17:12.378 --> 17:14.214
THERE'S A BODY.

17:14.214 --> 17:16.016
WHAT?

17:16.016 --> 17:17.117
YEAH.

17:19.119 --> 17:20.453
WHO IS IT?

17:23.389 --> 17:24.891
IT ‐‐ IT ‐‐ IT IS ‐‐

17:24.891 --> 17:27.561
HIS NAME IS QUINCY.

17:27.561 --> 17:29.663
MAXWELL?

17:29.663 --> 17:32.198
YEAH.

17:35.401 --> 17:39.072
WHAT'D YOU HAVE
TO DO WITH IT?

17:39.072 --> 17:40.907
I ‐‐ I ‐‐ I, UM...

17:40.907 --> 17:42.643
<i>TELL ME, JEFFERY.</i>

17:46.412 --> 17:49.783
I STABBED HIM.

17:53.620 --> 17:56.022
YOU GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

17:56.022 --> 17:58.058
JUST YOU?

17:58.058 --> 18:00.601
AND CANDACE.

18:02.969 --> 18:06.640
WAIT. HOW'D THIS HAPPEN?

18:06.640 --> 18:10.476
HE ‐‐ HE CAME INTO
THE HOUSE AND...

18:13.680 --> 18:15.782
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

18:15.782 --> 18:18.852
OH, COME ON.
YOU DON'T CARE.

18:18.852 --> 18:21.221
<i>JEFFERY, I'M TRYING</i>
<i>TO HELP YOU.</i>

18:21.221 --> 18:22.222
WELL, IT DOESN'T MATTER NOW.

18:22.222 --> 18:23.223
I ‐‐ I ‐‐ IT'S...

18:23.223 --> 18:24.490
NO, IT DOES.

18:24.490 --> 18:27.027
TELL ME EVERYTHING
RIGHT NOW.

18:30.531 --> 18:33.867
I STABBED HIM.

18:37.504 --> 18:39.573
AND CANDACE STABBED HIM.

18:41.942 --> 18:45.546
I MEAN, I WANTED
TO CALL THE POLICE.

18:45.546 --> 18:47.480
BUT SHE SAID
IT WOULD BE OVERKILL.

18:49.449 --> 18:52.452
SO...

18:52.452 --> 18:53.820
I DIDN'T.

18:54.788 --> 18:59.192
UM, AND, UH...

18:59.192 --> 19:05.639
SHE JUST BURIED
THE BODY IN THE BACKYARD.

19:05.639 --> 19:07.541
THIS IS THE DUMBEST THING
I'VE EVER HEARD.

19:07.541 --> 19:09.342
<i>I ‐‐ I DON'T KNOW</i>
<i>WHAT TO DO.</i>

19:09.342 --> 19:10.877
WELL, YOU SHOULD'VE GONE
TO THE POLICE.

19:10.877 --> 19:12.278
I KNOW.
BUT SHE SAID THAT ‐‐

19:12.278 --> 19:15.582
THAT ‐‐ THAT THEY WOULD THINK
THAT WE DID IT ON PURPOSE.

19:15.582 --> 19:17.250
GOSH DAMN IT.

19:19.853 --> 19:23.557
OH, GOD,
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

19:23.557 --> 19:26.760
I DON'T THINK THERE'S
ANYTHING WE CAN DO.

19:26.760 --> 19:28.261
LOOK, I'LL STALL THEM
IN THE HOUSE.

19:28.261 --> 19:30.531
<i>BUT THERE'S A DAMN MUD PILE</i>
<i>IN THE BACKYARD.</i>

19:30.531 --> 19:32.132
<i>THEY'RE GONNA FIND IT.</i>

19:32.132 --> 19:34.635
I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW.

19:34.635 --> 19:35.769
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

19:35.769 --> 19:37.704
NO ‐‐ NO...

19:37.704 --> 19:39.706
WH ‐‐ WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

19:39.706 --> 19:41.241
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

19:53.019 --> 19:54.087
WHO DID YOU KILL?

19:56.990 --> 19:57.991
WYATT?

19:57.991 --> 20:00.634
DAMN...WHO'D YOU KILL?

20:02.102 --> 20:04.204
WHAT ‐‐ YOU'RE ‐‐
YOU'RE AWAKE!

20:04.204 --> 20:06.006
WH ‐‐ HEY, HOW ARE YOU ‐‐
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

20:06.006 --> 20:07.240
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

20:07.240 --> 20:10.711
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

20:10.711 --> 20:13.547
WHERE THE HELL AM I? DAMN.

20:13.547 --> 20:14.815
YOU'RE IN THE HOSPITAL.

20:17.250 --> 20:19.686
OKAY.

20:19.686 --> 20:21.655
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

20:21.655 --> 20:22.689
JUST...GETTING OUT OF HERE.

20:22.689 --> 20:23.690
STOP. WOULD YOU STOP?

20:23.690 --> 20:24.758
I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.

20:24.758 --> 20:26.560
NO, NO, NO.
LET ME GO GET A DOCTOR.

20:26.560 --> 20:28.161
JUST STAY STILL.
JUST LET ME ‐‐

20:28.161 --> 20:29.329
LET ME GET A DOCTOR.

20:29.329 --> 20:30.831
[ Whispering ] MOVE.

20:30.831 --> 20:32.899
WYATT, JUST SIT BACK,
SIT BACK, SIT BACK.

20:32.899 --> 20:33.967
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

20:33.967 --> 20:35.502
[ GROANS ]

20:35.502 --> 20:37.203
SEE? TAKE IT ‐‐

20:37.203 --> 20:38.839
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED TO ME?

20:38.839 --> 20:40.741
YOU OVERDOSED.

20:40.741 --> 20:42.509
STAY HERE.
WHAT?

20:42.509 --> 20:45.045
YEAH, WE THOUGHT
YOU WERE DEAD.

20:47.948 --> 20:49.249
DAMN.

20:49.249 --> 20:51.017
WYATT, YOU HAVE TO PROMISE
NEVER TO SCARE ME

20:51.017 --> 20:53.587
LIKE THAT AGAIN.

20:53.587 --> 20:55.055
I ALMOST DIED?

20:55.055 --> 20:57.223
YEAH.

20:57.223 --> 20:59.726
OH, DAMN.

21:04.938 --> 21:06.707
I NEED TO TAKE
MORE NEXT TIME.

21:06.707 --> 21:08.975
OH, WOULD YOU STOP IT.
JUST STOP IT.

21:08.975 --> 21:11.011
I'M KIDDING, MAN.

21:11.011 --> 21:13.179
SAD PART IS, YOU'RE NOT.

21:18.752 --> 21:23.724
SO...YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHO YOU KILLED?

21:25.425 --> 21:28.061
WAIT, NO ‐‐ NO.
YOU DIDN'T HEAR ME SAY THAT.

21:28.061 --> 21:29.663
YEAH. YEAH, I DID.

21:29.663 --> 21:33.934
NO, LET ME JUST
GET YOU A DOCTOR.

21:33.934 --> 21:35.201
I'M FINE.

21:35.201 --> 21:37.738
[INDISTINCT]
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

21:37.738 --> 21:39.439
I'M FINE.
I'M FINE!

21:39.439 --> 21:42.943
[ GRUNTING ]

21:51.552 --> 21:54.487
YOU NEVER TOUCHED
YOUR DINNER.

21:54.487 --> 21:56.156
[ SNIFFLES ]

21:57.457 --> 22:00.634
NO.

22:00.634 --> 22:02.803
CAN'T EAT?

22:02.803 --> 22:04.304
MNH‐MNH

22:04.304 --> 22:07.373
WELL, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

22:07.373 --> 22:09.109
YOUR APPETITE
WILL COME BACK.

22:11.477 --> 22:13.847
WHY ARE YOU SO COOL
ABOUT ALL OF THIS?

22:13.847 --> 22:16.683
WHAT YOU WANT ME
TO DO, BABY?

22:16.683 --> 22:19.753
I DON'T KNOW,
GET MAD OR SOMETHING.

22:19.753 --> 22:22.155
ABOUT WHAT?

22:22.155 --> 22:25.258
I DON'T KNOW, CANDACE.

22:25.258 --> 22:26.727
AND ME.

22:26.727 --> 22:29.395
LOST YOUR SECOND HOUSE.

22:29.395 --> 22:32.298
NO, BABY.

22:32.298 --> 22:33.800
YOU ARE GONNA DO
WHAT YOU WANT TO DO.

22:33.800 --> 22:35.702
I TRIED TO TELL YOU.
YOU WOULDN'T LISTEN.

22:35.702 --> 22:38.304
YEAH, I KNOW, MA.

22:38.304 --> 22:39.573
THAT'S MY SISTER.

22:39.573 --> 22:41.341
SO I TRIED.
I GUESS I'M A DUMMY.

22:41.341 --> 22:42.943
MM.

22:42.943 --> 22:46.112
WHEN HAS SHE EVER DONE
WHAT SHE SAID SHE WAS GONNA DO?

22:46.112 --> 22:47.948
I DON'T KNOW. SHE PAID OFF
THE MORTGAGE TO YOUR HOUSE.

22:47.948 --> 22:49.883
YEAH, WITH MONEY SHE EXTORTED
FROM SOMEBODY.

22:49.883 --> 22:51.017
STILL DID IT.

22:51.017 --> 22:53.754
MM‐HMM, SHE BETTER HAD
HAVE PAID OFF MY MORTGAGE.

22:53.754 --> 22:55.221
AND I DIDN'T KNOW YOU HAD
LET HER TAKE OUT

22:55.221 --> 22:57.758
THAT MORTGAGE ON A HOUSE
I SLAVED TO PAY FOR.

22:57.758 --> 22:59.292
THERE IT IS.

22:59.292 --> 23:00.701
I KNOW, MAMA.
GO ON, GET MAD.

23:00.701 --> 23:02.636
HERE IT COMES.

23:02.636 --> 23:04.470
NO, HONEY.

23:04.470 --> 23:07.473
I GOT A PEACE
THAT HAS COME OVER ME

23:07.473 --> 23:10.611
THAT PASSES
ALL UNDERSTANDING.

23:10.611 --> 23:13.279
I'M GONNA DO MY BEST
TO HOLD ONTO IT.

23:13.279 --> 23:15.081
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

23:17.017 --> 23:18.451
WELL, IN A FEW MINUTES,
I'M GONNA GO UP THERE

23:18.451 --> 23:20.386
AND PACK THE LAST FEW
CLOTHES THAT I DO HAVE.

23:20.386 --> 23:22.623
FOR WHAT? GO WHERE?
WHERE WE GONNA GO?

23:22.623 --> 23:25.191
I DON'T KNOW.

23:25.191 --> 23:26.927
I STILL GOT
ABOUT $300 LEFT.

23:26.927 --> 23:31.898
AND WE CAN GO TO A HOTEL
FOR A WEEK WITH THAT.

23:31.898 --> 23:33.667
IT MAY NOT BE NICE,
BUT IT'LL BE SOMETHING.

23:33.667 --> 23:35.502
MOM.

23:35.502 --> 23:36.970
LOOK, BENNY...
IT'S SOMETHING.

23:36.970 --> 23:40.541
BABY, WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR ALL OF THIS.

23:42.643 --> 23:45.646
LISTEN TO ME.

23:45.646 --> 23:50.150
THIS IS HOW LIFE
GOES SOMETIMES.

23:50.150 --> 23:53.754
YOUR SISTER,
SHE WILL NEVER LEARN.

23:53.754 --> 23:55.589
SHE WON'T.

23:57.157 --> 24:00.293
WHY WOULD SHE DO THIS?

24:00.293 --> 24:02.736
I DON'T KNOW.

24:02.736 --> 24:05.005
BUT AS I SAID BEFORE,

24:05.005 --> 24:06.507
AS LONG AS YOU
KEEP TRUSTING IN HER,

24:06.507 --> 24:08.742
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO BELIEVE
IN NOTHING HIGHER.

24:11.177 --> 24:12.212
[ KNOCKING ]

24:14.314 --> 24:16.683
WELL, THAT MUST BE THEM.

24:16.683 --> 24:19.352
NO, WE GOT TILL
5:00 TOMORROW.

24:19.352 --> 24:21.287
THAT'S WHEN YOU HAVE?

24:21.287 --> 24:23.857
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

24:23.857 --> 24:27.327
OH.

24:27.327 --> 24:28.595
HI, BENNY.

24:31.164 --> 24:32.899
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

24:32.899 --> 24:34.535
I CAN'T GET THE MONEY, B.

24:34.535 --> 24:35.869
I'VE BEEN TRYING.

24:35.869 --> 24:38.905
OH. I KNOW THAT.

24:38.905 --> 24:40.541
BUT I CALLED MR. BOWMAN.

24:40.541 --> 24:44.010
AND HE GAVE ME THE OPTION
TO TURN MYSELF IN.

24:44.010 --> 24:46.346
AND IF I DO THAT, MAYBE
WE COULD KEEP THE MORTGAGE.

24:46.346 --> 24:48.749
MAYBE, HUH.
SO ALL'S WELL NOW, I GUESS.

24:57.457 --> 24:59.660
DIDN'T KNOW YOU'D BE HERE.

24:59.660 --> 25:01.067
OH, YES.

25:01.067 --> 25:03.837
I AM.

25:03.837 --> 25:05.906
TILL ABOUT 5:00
TOMORROW.

25:08.542 --> 25:10.611
WE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

25:10.611 --> 25:11.612
MM‐HMM.

25:11.612 --> 25:12.613
TURN YOURSELF
IN FOR WHAT?

25:12.613 --> 25:13.614
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

25:13.614 --> 25:15.448
DON'T TELL ME THEN.

25:15.448 --> 25:16.449
I WON'T.

25:16.449 --> 25:17.684
YOU KNOW WHAT,
STOP IT, DAMN IT.

25:17.684 --> 25:18.785
RIGHT NOW. YOU STOP IT.

25:18.785 --> 25:20.253
BENNY.
THAT BABY'S UPSTAIRS.

25:20.253 --> 25:23.223
AND I DON'T WANT HIM
TO HEAR NONE OF THIS.

25:23.223 --> 25:25.892
GO ON, TELL HER WHAT YOU GONNA
TURN YOURSELF IN FOR, CANDACE.

25:25.892 --> 25:28.161
NO.

25:28.161 --> 25:30.764
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU'RE A COWARD.

25:30.764 --> 25:32.332
FALSIFYING DOCUMENTS
AT THE BANK.

25:32.332 --> 25:35.569
THAT'S WHAT SHE DID.

25:35.569 --> 25:38.204
AND SHE SEEMS TO THINK
IF SHE TURNS HERSELF

25:38.204 --> 25:40.373
IN SHE GONNA BUY US
SOME TIME.

25:40.373 --> 25:41.708
AIN'T THAT RIGHT?

25:41.708 --> 25:44.377
I CAN GET HIM TO DO IT.

25:44.377 --> 25:45.912
WHO IS HIM?

25:45.912 --> 25:47.380
THE BANKER.

25:47.380 --> 25:50.617
I CAN CHANGE HIS MIND.

25:50.617 --> 25:53.186
YOU GONNA TRY
AND SLEEP WITH HIM, TOO?

25:53.186 --> 25:56.857
YEAH, I AM.

25:56.857 --> 25:58.324
BUT IF THAT DOESN'T WORK
I'M GONNA SEE

25:58.324 --> 26:01.267
WHAT OTHER BANKERS
WORK THERE WHO WILL.

26:01.267 --> 26:02.636
MAYBE THEIR WIVES
WILL DO IT,

26:02.636 --> 26:04.370
YOU KNOW WHAT, I'M NOT IN THE
MOOD FOR YOUR FILTH.

26:04.370 --> 26:05.371
SHUT UP.

26:05.371 --> 26:06.372
BENJAMIN.
TELL HER TO STOP.

26:06.372 --> 26:07.373
YOU STOP IT.

26:07.373 --> 26:09.342
BENJAMIN, WATCH YOUR MOUTH.

26:09.342 --> 26:11.344
SEE? I'M TELLING YOU.

26:11.344 --> 26:13.346
SHE WON'T LEARN!

26:13.346 --> 26:14.347
SHE WON'T.

26:14.347 --> 26:16.216
I'M STARTING
TO THINK SHE CAN'T.

26:16.216 --> 26:20.320
SHE GONNA TRY AND CON THIS MAN
INTO LETTING YOU STAY HERE.

26:20.320 --> 26:22.989
OOH, YEAH.
IT NEVER ENDS.

26:22.989 --> 26:25.158
IT NEVER ENDS
AT ALL, EVER.

26:26.860 --> 26:29.763
BENNY, I'M GONNA TURN MYSELF IN
FOR THE BOTH OF US, OKAY?

26:29.763 --> 26:32.566
OKAY. YOU DID THIS,
GO PAY FOR IT.

26:32.566 --> 26:34.434
YOU THINK I WON'T?
I KNOW YOU WON'T.

26:34.434 --> 26:36.503
'CAUSE THAT WOULD MEAN TAKING
RESPONSIBILITY FOR SOMETHING.

26:36.503 --> 26:37.638
AND THAT'S SOMETHING
YOU CAN'T DO.

26:37.638 --> 26:39.372
MAMA.
DAMN IT.

26:39.372 --> 26:41.241
YOUR MOUTH
ONE MORE TIME, BENJAMIN.

26:41.241 --> 26:42.743
COME ON!

26:42.743 --> 26:44.410
SHE'S LYING.

26:44.410 --> 26:46.312
YOU MEAN TO TELL ME YOU STILL
CAN'T TELL WHEN SHE'S LYING?

26:46.312 --> 26:47.748
SHE AIN'T GONNA
GO DO THIS, BENJAMIN.

26:47.748 --> 26:49.583
GO UPSTAIRS AND PACK
YOUR CLOTHES 'FORE THESE PEOPLE

26:49.583 --> 26:51.351
COME AND THROW YOUR STUFF
OUT ON THE STREET.

26:51.351 --> 26:53.319
HOPEFULLY, YOU WON'T
HAVE TO.

26:53.319 --> 26:56.422
I AM GOING TO
TURN MYSELF IN. I AM.

26:56.422 --> 26:57.591
LOOK.

26:57.591 --> 26:59.092
NOBODY'S ASKING YOU TO DO THAT.

26:59.092 --> 27:00.126
B...

27:00.126 --> 27:01.668
I'LL GIVE IT UP.
I'LL GIVE ALL THIS UP.

27:01.668 --> 27:03.069
THERE YOU JUST FELL
FOR ANOTHER LIE.

27:03.069 --> 27:04.605
WELL, WHAT, I DON'T HAVE
NO CHOICE HERE, MA.

27:04.605 --> 27:06.272
YEAH, YOU DO.

27:06.272 --> 27:08.341
WHAT, LET HER GO TO JAIL?
I AIN'T LETTING HER GO TO JAIL.

27:08.341 --> 27:09.910
IF YOU DON'T GO TO JAIL
FOR THIS YOU GONNA PROBABLY

27:09.910 --> 27:11.612
GO TO JAIL FOR QUINCY.

27:15.148 --> 27:16.149
WHAT?

27:16.149 --> 27:17.250
THAT WOMAN
OVER THERE SAID

27:17.250 --> 27:18.484
SHE NEVER SAW HIM
COME OUT OF YOUR HOUSE.

27:18.484 --> 27:20.153
WHERE IS HE?

27:25.158 --> 27:29.730
WHY WOULD YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHERE HE IS?

27:29.730 --> 27:32.265
I'M WORRIED FOR YOU, GIRL.

27:34.267 --> 27:36.603
I'M NOT DOING THIS.

27:36.603 --> 27:38.605
LOOK, YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO JAIL.

27:39.806 --> 27:40.941
BENNY.

27:40.941 --> 27:42.442
I KNOW YOU DON'T THINK
I'M GONNA SIT HERE

27:42.442 --> 27:44.911
AND WATCH HER WALK
HERSELF INTO JAIL.

27:44.911 --> 27:46.279
I'M NOT.

27:46.279 --> 27:49.983
HOW'S SHE GONNA LEARN?
WHEN WILL SHE LEARN?

27:49.983 --> 27:51.217
I'M STANDING RIGHT HERE.

27:51.217 --> 27:53.286
WHEN ARE YOU
GOING TO LEARN?

27:56.590 --> 27:59.860
YOU CAN DO
WHAT YOU WANT, OKAY?

27:59.860 --> 28:02.803
YOU CAN LIVE YOUR LIFE
THE WAY YOU WANT TO.

28:02.803 --> 28:05.171
BUT THERE'S MORE
TO THIS LIFE FOR ME.

28:05.171 --> 28:06.940
YES, THERE IS, CANDACE.
THERE IS MORE TO LIFE,

28:06.940 --> 28:08.374
BUT NOT THE WAY
YOU DOING IT.

28:11.545 --> 28:14.047
I'M GONNA GET IT,
OKAY, BENNY?

28:14.047 --> 28:15.415
I'M GONNA GO HOME.

28:15.415 --> 28:19.119
I HAVE ABOUT $20K
IN A SAFE THERE.

28:19.119 --> 28:21.154
AND I'M GONNA SELL
SOME THINGS.

28:21.154 --> 28:23.356
AND THEN I'LL BE BACK.
AND I'LL HEAD TO THE BANK.

28:23.356 --> 28:24.891
NO.

28:24.891 --> 28:27.260
IF I HAVE TO GO AWAY,
THEN I'LL GO AWAY.

28:27.260 --> 28:28.261
NO!

28:28.261 --> 28:30.030
BENNY, SHE IS LYING.

28:30.030 --> 28:31.565
[ SIGHS ]

28:38.505 --> 28:40.173
I'LL BE BACK, BENNY.

28:42.943 --> 28:45.946
Y'ALL DON'T GET IT.

28:45.946 --> 28:47.413
OOH, Y'ALL DON'T GET IT.

29:02.268 --> 29:05.606
I NEED TO MAKE THIS HAPPEN.

29:05.606 --> 29:08.341
DAVID.

29:08.341 --> 29:10.143
CHARLES!

29:10.143 --> 29:11.144
HOW ARE YOU?

29:11.144 --> 29:12.713
I'M WELL.

29:12.713 --> 29:14.180
MAN, ARE YOU SURE?

29:14.180 --> 29:16.116
YES, I'M FINE.

29:16.116 --> 29:18.084
I'VE BEEN HEARING ABOUT
ALL THAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU.

29:18.084 --> 29:19.953
YES, AND I'VE BEEN HEARING
AND READING ABOUT YOU.

29:19.953 --> 29:22.589
CONGRATULATIONS.
THANK YOU.

29:22.589 --> 29:24.124
LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE GONNA BE
OUR NEXT PRESIDENT.

29:24.124 --> 29:26.627
OH, COME ON. WE STILL HAVE
A LONG WAY TO GO.

29:26.627 --> 29:28.762
FOUR WEEKS IS NOT
A LONG WAY.

29:28.762 --> 29:30.496
WELL, I MEAN ‐‐
YOU ARE IN THE LEAD.

29:30.496 --> 29:32.265
YOU ARE GOING TO WIN.

29:32.265 --> 29:34.801
THANK YOU.

29:34.801 --> 29:36.469
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

29:36.469 --> 29:38.171
DRUMMING UP VOTES
FOR THE CAMPAIGN.

29:38.171 --> 29:39.740
AH, YES. OF COURSE.

29:39.740 --> 29:41.675
OH. YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?

29:41.675 --> 29:43.109
YES, I DO.

29:43.109 --> 29:44.110
I'M SORRY.

29:44.110 --> 29:45.111
I COULDN'T CALL ON YOU.

29:45.111 --> 29:47.247
NO, NO, THAT'S FINE.

29:47.247 --> 29:48.715
MY SITUATION IS TOO HOT.

29:48.715 --> 29:51.852
IT WOULDN'T BE GOOD
FOR YOU TO BE SEEN WITH ME.

29:51.852 --> 29:53.353
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN
A GOOD FRIEND.

29:53.353 --> 29:56.456
YES, WELL, YOU ARE RUNNING FOR
PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES.

29:56.456 --> 29:57.991
IT IS NOT GONNA
HELP YOUR CAMPAIGN

